Review this loop for a resource issue:
```go
func poll(ch <-chan int) {
	for {
		select {
		case v := <-ch:
			process(v)
		case <-time.After(time.Second):
			return
		}
	}
}
```

response:
**Bug: `time.After` in a loop leaks a timer every iteration.** Each `select` builds a *new* `time.After` channel+timer; the timer isn't garbage-collected until it fires (up to a second later), so a hot loop accumulates thousands of live timers. Worse, the timeout never represents "a second of total inactivity" — it resets every time a value arrives.

Create one `time.Timer` and reset it, stopping it on exit:

```go
func poll(ch <-chan int) {
	t := time.NewTimer(time.Second)
	defer t.Stop()
	for {
		select {
		case v := <-ch:
			process(v)
			if !t.Stop() {
				<-t.C
			}
			t.Reset(time.Second)
		case <-t.C:
			return
		}
	}
}
```

